  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Ishraq in Islam?",
  "response": "In Islam, Ishraq refers to the time of day shortly after sunrise. It is also associated with a specific prayer called the Ishraq prayer or Duha prayer. Muslims perform this optional prayer about 20 minutes to half an hour after the sun has fully risen. This prayer consists of two rak'ahs (units of prayer) and is considered highly virtuous, as it brings blessings and spiritual rewards. Ishraq prayer is a part of Salat al-Duha, which can be prayed until just before the sun reaches its zenith.",
